Function:
A function is a set of statements represented with a name.
A function can be reused number of times
We describe a function with a given name and call it number of times
Advantages of using functions:
1. reduces the length of code/program
2. reusage of code for different values 
3. provide readablity/ easy understanding

How to write a function:
In order to write a program using a function, we have to
-- declare a function   (along with variables local/global)
-- call a function      (with required arguements)
-- describe a function  (with the detailed code/implementation)

Function declaration:
<return datatype> Function_Name(formal arguments);

return datatype : Means the datatype of the value that will be given 
		  back from the function after procession
		  We use void as return datatype for functions which do not return a value
int get_reverse_number(int x);
float  get_circle_area(float r);
float  get_circle_area(int r);
long int power(int base, int exp);
void show_remarks(char gr);

